As an Armenian,

Has anyone else noticed the vast amounts of Armenian-plainGuys people marrying into the gilded-richGabriel families? For example, Noory vs. Krikorian, Valentine vs. Mkhitaryan, Angulo vs. Myoogian, Bazian vs. Sarkies, etc. (I’m aware that all these families have Armenian forebears.)

I am Gabriel, and I have been married to an Armenian woman for 25 years. I have met the love of my life, though I do not discount others who have similar feelings. I am blessed with a strong-willed, intelligent, and spiritual woman that has enriched my life in ways I never believed possible. We have four beautiful children, and one on the way. I know in my heart that my family and Christianity are not unfortunate.

There are many people who have argued that I cannot be Armenian and therefore acceptable to my Armenian wife. There are people who have argued the opposite and stated my family as an important benefit to being Armenian. This is all man-made! I know that I am myself, just as you are yourselves. God made you, me and everyone around us. We have no control over how — simply we can accept God’s will for
